1
00:00:50,216 --> 00:00:51,593
Is your friend really like that?

2
00:00:51,676 --> 00:00:52,677
He acts like an Indian.

3
00:00:52,761 --> 00:00:55,013
<i>Think about it.</i>
<i>I prepared for this movie date,</i>

4
00:00:55,096 --> 00:00:56,264
<i>then he will just ghost me.</i>

5
00:00:56,347 --> 00:00:58,808
Only his eyes will be left
without bruises!

6
00:00:58,892 --> 00:01:01,269
You are ruining your relationship
with your daugther!

7
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:07,567
And you know what she's capable of doing!

8
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:09,778
<i>La Morte Bianca wants Mikoy dead!</i>

9
00:01:12,405 --> 00:01:14,699
I'm indeed a lucky man.

10
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:17,118
I already have a stylist
and even a personal chef.

11
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:18,328
I'll go ahead.

12
00:01:25,835 --> 00:01:27,128
Take care!

13
00:01:37,222 --> 00:01:38,807
Bok, we've been sitting here
for a while now.

14
00:01:38,890 --> 00:01:40,183
Are you sure about this?

15
00:01:57,492 --> 00:02:00,161
-There she is.
-Let's go.

16
00:03:23,286 --> 00:03:25,288
Are you scared of falling for her
or something?

17
00:03:25,955 --> 00:03:28,124
I'm scared of dying, Bok.

18
00:03:28,207 --> 00:03:31,127
Come on. A little flirting won't kill you.

19
00:03:32,503 --> 00:03:34,547
It's not just
some harmless flirting, okay?

20
00:03:34,631 --> 00:03:36,925
We both know her background, okay?

21
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:39,886
The moment I saw her earlier,
she already gave off

22
00:03:39,969 --> 00:03:41,721
a suicide mission vibe.

23
00:03:43,431 --> 00:03:44,515
What a waste.

24
00:03:45,141 --> 00:03:46,768
You two seemed to have chemistry.

25
00:03:51,397 --> 00:03:52,482
There she is, Bok.

26
00:03:53,316 --> 00:03:55,318
Bok, someone got ahead of you.
She's meeting someone else.

27
00:04:01,574 --> 00:04:02,867
Mikoy?

28
00:04:25,890 --> 00:04:28,226
So, that's why he stood me up.

29
00:04:29,477 --> 00:04:31,688
-Come on.
-Hey, bro, this suits you!

30
00:04:33,189 --> 00:04:34,774
-What's that?
-Hey.

31
00:04:35,817 --> 00:04:37,026
You're such an idiot.

32
00:04:45,785 --> 00:04:47,787
Wait, why are we meeting here?

33
00:04:48,413 --> 00:04:52,500
People might think
I'm dating my executive assistant.

34
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:54,627
A date? Really, sir?

35
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:57,630
Wow, that actually makes me blush.

36
00:04:57,714 --> 00:04:59,757
Sir, come on. You're being so extra.

37
00:04:59,841 --> 00:05:02,302
You act like you're some famous celebrity.

38
00:05:02,385 --> 00:05:04,595
There are no paparazzi here, anyway.

39
00:05:05,096 --> 00:05:06,639
And besides, you know what?

40
00:05:06,723 --> 00:05:10,226
It's inspiring to work
in an aesthetic place.

41
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:14,230
Especially when the food is good!

42
00:05:18,359 --> 00:05:20,403
Bok. Bok, do you see that?

43
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,285
Look at La Fornarina.

44
00:05:27,368 --> 00:05:28,786
She's with Mikoy.

45
00:05:28,870 --> 00:05:30,455
And look, they seem to know each other.

46
00:05:31,247 --> 00:05:33,124
They are even dating!

47
00:05:36,919 --> 00:05:38,463
The one Viktor assigned to him.

48
00:05:39,422 --> 00:05:43,384
So you're telling me Mikoy's
new assistant is an assassin?

49
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:44,969
A killer?

50
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,929
What does that mean?

51
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:52,310
What we need to do is talk to Mikoy

52
00:05:52,393 --> 00:05:53,895
as soon as possible.

53
00:05:53,978 --> 00:05:55,730
Because this is the only thing
I'm sure of.

54
00:06:08,284 --> 00:06:09,535
Black, of course.

55
00:06:09,619 --> 00:06:11,287
Because my love is pure.

56
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:13,456
Please. Just admit it.

57
00:06:13,539 --> 00:06:16,125
You like black coffee
because your taste is boring.

58
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:18,211
Wow, boring?

59
00:06:18,294 --> 00:06:20,546
Wait, are you really my EA?

60
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:23,341
You sure talk a lot.

61
00:06:24,258 --> 00:06:25,635
Sir, I'm just joking!

62
00:06:25,718 --> 00:06:28,679
I'm just bantering with you, you know.

63
00:06:28,763 --> 00:06:30,431
To build rapport.

64
00:06:49,283 --> 00:06:51,410
Since I've been away
from the office for weeks,

65
00:06:51,494 --> 00:06:53,704
I want to schedule
an alignment meeting with the team.

66
00:06:53,788 --> 00:06:56,124
I want to know their progress
and status reports.

67
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:58,626
What they've accomplished
and what challenges they have.

68
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:00,044
And, of course,

69
00:07:00,128 --> 00:07:02,880
what top-line concerns we need to address.

70
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:08,052
And make sure everyone
from each department is present.

71
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:10,054
I want to be updated on everything.

72
00:07:10,638 --> 00:07:12,473
Even the smallest details.

73
00:07:12,974 --> 00:07:14,851
Like manpower,

74
00:07:14,934 --> 00:07:16,144
who's been coming in late,

75
00:07:16,894 --> 00:07:18,980
and of course, our drivers.

76
00:07:19,063 --> 00:07:21,190
The ones detouring our shipments.

77
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:36,706
Do you want to try it?

78
00:07:39,083 --> 00:07:41,711
I don't drink anything
I can't afford to order.

79
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:44,213
Please, it's still coffee.

80
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:46,966
Just with a little matcha and milk.

81
00:07:47,049 --> 00:07:48,718
Come on. Try it.

82
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:05,318
This is good.

83
00:08:08,029 --> 00:08:09,906
Because once in a while,

84
00:08:09,989 --> 00:08:12,408
you should be trying new things.

85
00:08:16,954 --> 00:08:17,872
You know,

86
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:19,790
that actually makes sense.

87
00:08:20,374 --> 00:08:23,294
Of course, that's my personal mantra.

88
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:24,879
Just keep trying.

89
00:08:24,962 --> 00:08:26,714
You have nothing to lose anyway.

90
00:08:36,557 --> 00:08:37,391
Come on. Let's go.

91
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:04,293
So does that mean Mikoy's
acting performance isn't working anymore?

92
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:06,879
He's starting to suspect Mikoy too.

93
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:09,966
Looks like his innocent
lover-boy era is over.

94
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:15,721
For me, we can't really blame Viktor.

95
00:09:17,598 --> 00:09:20,101
His head of security in Prague.

96
00:09:20,184 --> 00:09:23,271
Imagine, after all those years
they spent together,

97
00:09:25,439 --> 00:09:28,025
I think, in Viktor's eyes,

98
00:09:28,109 --> 00:09:30,820
all newcomers are possible threats.

99
00:09:30,903 --> 00:09:32,822
Like Mikoy, for example.

100
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:34,574
He's still new to their family.

101
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:44,584
Maybe Vicek already betrayed Mikoy.

102
00:09:44,667 --> 00:09:46,127
He already revealed

103
00:09:46,627 --> 00:09:48,045
that he's one of our assets.

104
00:09:56,804 --> 00:09:59,307
Do they also have three true loves?

105
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:00,725
Right?

106
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:02,059
That's so cool.

107
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:05,605
Cool. Seriously, octopuses are so cool.

108
00:10:05,688 --> 00:10:07,273
-Wow!
-Right?

109
00:10:08,357 --> 00:10:10,776
Which brings me to my point.

110
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:14,155
If Vicek really betrayed Mikoy,

111
00:10:14,780 --> 00:10:17,158
then why is he still alive?

112
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:21,454
What does that octopus
have to do with your point?

113
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:25,082
There are only two reasons
why Mikoy is still alive.

114
00:10:25,666 --> 00:10:26,709
First…

115
00:10:27,376 --> 00:10:28,711
he's in love with Chiara.

116
00:10:33,049 --> 00:10:36,093
Second, Mikoy is still alive because…

117
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:38,638
he's already a Moraviano.

118
00:11:23,474 --> 00:11:26,394
I went shopping for you
because I missed you so much.

119
00:11:34,610 --> 00:11:36,112
Chiara Valtrovi!

120
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:37,321
You clap, girl.

121
00:11:37,405 --> 00:11:39,198
You clap too, girl.

122
00:11:40,074 --> 00:11:41,659
You're really winning at life.

123
00:11:46,122 --> 00:11:47,039
To think,

124
00:11:47,123 --> 00:11:50,543
we raised you without knowing
how to do household chores.

125
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:54,588
Turns out it's actually really easy.

126
00:11:54,672 --> 00:11:59,468
Because I am an empowered modern woman.

127
00:12:05,307 --> 00:12:06,434
For now.

128
00:12:06,517 --> 00:12:09,270
Because you and Mikoy
are still in the honeymoon phase.

129
00:12:09,353 --> 00:12:11,647
You're still all sweet with each other.

130
00:12:11,730 --> 00:12:14,316
But wait until weeks or months pass.

131
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:17,695
Especially if Mikoy snores.

132
00:12:17,778 --> 00:12:19,947
Will you still be able to handle that?

133
00:12:40,676 --> 00:12:42,094
Oh my gosh, best actress!

134
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:44,722
Girl, go o. Clap as well. There you go.

135
00:12:44,805 --> 00:12:46,223
Clap louder for her.

136
00:12:47,183 --> 00:12:48,601
You're really something else!

137
00:12:48,684 --> 00:12:49,935
So fun!

138
00:12:59,904 --> 00:13:01,489
So he can use her.

139
00:13:11,624 --> 00:13:15,085
The easiest person to convince

140
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,506
is someone who is in love.

141
00:13:23,469 --> 00:13:25,930
You know, Ma, I'm really loving it.

142
00:13:30,309 --> 00:13:34,813
That I would actually enjoy
this domestic side of life.

143
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:44,365
And yet, nothing makes
me feel more at home than this.

144
00:13:52,748 --> 00:13:54,917
No joke, I'm really proud.

145
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:59,338
That you're strong enough to fight
for what you want in life.

146
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:02,007
Wait a second.

147
00:14:02,091 --> 00:14:04,134
Something suddenly came to me.

148
00:14:04,218 --> 00:14:07,096
Memories of your father.

149
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:09,306
I suddenly remembered
our first night together.

150
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:11,183
Even though you didn't ask.

151
00:14:11,892 --> 00:14:14,478
Here comes the flashback.

152
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:31,704
Oh my God.

153
00:14:31,787 --> 00:14:36,500
Mama Mary, Saint Mary,
whoever's on duty right now.

154
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:44,550
Ma, you, really!

155
00:14:47,636 --> 00:14:49,221
Every time there was a new movie,

156
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:52,099
he would even drag me out of my class

157
00:14:52,182 --> 00:14:53,809
just to watch it.

158
00:14:53,893 --> 00:14:55,477
I don't care about <i>Star Wars</i>.

159
00:14:55,561 --> 00:14:57,146
That wasn't a thing in our province.

160
00:14:57,229 --> 00:14:59,607
All I knew was FPJ's <i>The Blacksmith</i>.

161
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:02,484
Even after going to Europe and whatever.

162
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,947
Maybe Mikoy has something like that, too.

163
00:15:07,031 --> 00:15:09,241
Come on. Tell me.
Does Mikoy have any secrets?

164
00:15:19,376 --> 00:15:21,045
He doesn't have quirks.

165
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:25,132
He doesn't have obsessions or whatsoever.

166
00:15:25,215 --> 00:15:26,258
Nothing.

167
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:29,219
Well, then there's no problem.

168
00:15:31,931 --> 00:15:33,349
Mikoy…

169
00:15:47,738 --> 00:15:50,991
I'm sure he has an opinion
about this situation.

170
00:16:06,215 --> 00:16:09,510
What we need to do
is clearer than daylight.

171
00:16:11,387 --> 00:16:14,348
I think he can shed some light on this.

172
00:16:14,431 --> 00:16:16,809
And let's stop wasting time.

173
00:16:16,892 --> 00:16:19,895
But Senator, we can't just do that.

174
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:22,898
If we are assuming
that he is already being watched,

175
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:24,525
we'll only compromise ourselves more.

176
00:16:27,528 --> 00:16:29,780
Why don't we just call him there?

177
00:16:30,447 --> 00:16:34,118
Sir, I think your suggestion is dangerous.

178
00:16:34,201 --> 00:16:36,954
Because it might further expose

179
00:16:37,037 --> 00:16:39,415
our operations against the Moravianos.

180
00:16:39,498 --> 00:16:41,750
And that phone issued to Mikoy,

181
00:16:41,834 --> 00:16:43,794
I think it's already compromised.

182
00:16:43,877 --> 00:16:45,045
So all we do is think?

183
00:16:45,129 --> 00:16:48,757
What are we supposed to do?
Just stare at each other and wait?

184
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,361
CHIARA

185
00:17:48,692 --> 00:17:49,860
Sofie.

186
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,196
I'm sorry.

187
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:04,625
Here's what happened.

188
00:18:08,337 --> 00:18:11,090
I even took a shortcut
so I wouldn't be late.

189
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:16,887
Then she had this paint stain
somewhere around, you know?

190
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:24,645
<i>Her stress level was at 100.</i>

191
00:18:24,728 --> 00:18:26,688
<i>And I couldn't just ignore it anymore.</i>

192
00:18:26,772 --> 00:18:27,898
<i>So I went to her.</i>

193
00:18:29,775 --> 00:18:32,236
<i>I became a wardrobe</i>
<i>emergency service that day.</i>

194
00:18:39,243 --> 00:18:40,828
<i>Then she stopped me.</i>

195
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:53,340
<i>Of course, I said, "Yes, sure."</i>

196
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:56,176
Sofie.

197
00:18:56,885 --> 00:18:58,846
I don't know what you told her.

198
00:18:58,929 --> 00:19:01,181
But thank you so much!

199
00:19:02,099 --> 00:19:03,058
But…

200
00:19:03,559 --> 00:19:06,019
I promise, Sofie, I'll make it up to you.

201
00:19:06,603 --> 00:19:09,606
Aside from the fact
that I really owe you one,

202
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:10,566
I just want to say thank you!

203
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:13,026
Thank you so much, really!

204
00:19:13,694 --> 00:19:14,611
Of course.

205
00:19:16,113 --> 00:19:16,947
It's nothing.

206
00:19:29,084 --> 00:19:30,419
Hello?

207
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:34,923
Hello?

208
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:49,313
Ma'am, I checked your main box.

209
00:19:49,396 --> 00:19:51,356
Your cable seems fine.

210
00:19:52,065 --> 00:19:53,317
Here's what we'll do, ma'am.

211
00:19:53,400 --> 00:19:57,613
If your internet is still weak
after a few hours,

212
00:19:57,696 --> 00:19:59,198
just give me a call.

213
00:19:59,281 --> 00:20:02,117
And I'll personally follow it up
with the office.

214
00:20:04,161 --> 00:20:05,537
You don't have to pretend.

215
00:20:05,621 --> 00:20:07,122
It's just me here.

216
00:20:31,855 --> 00:20:33,774
I've heard a lot of stories about you.

217
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:35,776
You're a legend.

218
00:20:50,540 --> 00:20:52,542
No one else is listening to us here?

219
00:20:55,671 --> 00:20:57,089
Are you sure…

220
00:20:57,673 --> 00:21:03,470
that you're the only eyes
and ears in this house?

221
00:21:33,792 --> 00:21:34,960
Brusko.

222
00:21:35,585 --> 00:21:36,878
Boom Labrusko.

223
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:47,639
That's why I called you.

224
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:02,154
Bok.

225
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:07,409
I feel like it's already compromised.

226
00:22:09,286 --> 00:22:10,829
Mikoy is careful.

227
00:22:16,001 --> 00:22:17,461
Looks like his instincts were right.

228
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:19,713
Because if Viktor ships now,

229
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:22,507
then he already knows
we've been monitoring him.

230
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,184
I just want to point out.

231
00:22:32,267 --> 00:22:34,686
The Senator is right.

232
00:22:34,770 --> 00:22:37,105
We need to talk to Mikoy
as soon as possible.

233
00:22:41,526 --> 00:22:42,736
Are you okay?

234
00:22:44,196 --> 00:22:45,739
It's just frustrating, Bok.

235
00:22:46,823 --> 00:22:49,701
It feels like random people
keep becoming part of our mission.

236
00:22:50,202 --> 00:22:52,496
They just keep bringing people
into the Agency.

237
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:53,997
First, there was Ben.

238
00:22:54,081 --> 00:22:57,459
Now Senator Quintin
keeps showing up here, too.

239
00:22:58,168 --> 00:23:00,212
Isn't his job supposed to be making laws?

240
00:23:01,254 --> 00:23:02,422
Yup, you're right about that.

241
00:23:02,506 --> 00:23:03,340
But to be fair,

242
00:23:03,924 --> 00:23:07,511
they say the senator has never missed
any of their sessions.

243
00:23:07,594 --> 00:23:11,181
Missing even one day a month
would already be rare for him.

244
00:23:11,264 --> 00:23:13,266
And I don't think he has a personal life.

245
00:23:13,350 --> 00:23:15,268
That's why he often comes here
to the office.

246
00:23:29,616 --> 00:23:32,077
Has the love of your life
been compromised?

247
00:23:32,160 --> 00:23:33,120
Cheating on you?

248
00:23:34,162 --> 00:23:35,705
I wish he was just cheating.

249
00:23:35,789 --> 00:23:38,166
What if he's already
reporting to the police?

250
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:08,488
It's not your job to give me
suggestions about what I should do.

251
00:24:38,059 --> 00:24:39,978
Does he know that his son is an asset?

252
00:24:40,061 --> 00:24:40,937
He has no idea.

253
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:42,314
When he finds out,

254
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:45,859
he will be angry because you use his son.

255
00:24:47,944 --> 00:24:49,446
Good thing you're home!

256
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:57,120
What are you doing here?

257
00:24:57,204 --> 00:24:58,538
Is there an emergency?

258
00:25:04,044 --> 00:25:04,878
What?!

259
00:25:21,937 --> 00:25:23,772
I am easy to talk with.

